From: Ian Rogers <irogers@google.com>
Date: Tue, 29 Apr 2025 17:41:27 -0700
Subject: perf test demangle-java: Switch to using dso__demangle_sym()
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 41fcc9a3435f48c6d0948999491507b594f229a2
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
References: perf-sle16.1-v6.19-userspace-update

The use of the demangle-java APIs means we don't detect if a different
demangler is used before the Java one for the case that matters to
perf.

Remove the return types from the demangled names as dso__demangle_sym()
removes those.

